r,\nour data show RCS ~ v/2, much weaker than the normally assumed RCS ~ v^3, a\nconsequence of our requiring head echoes to also be detectable optically. Most\nevents show a smooth variation of RCS with height broadly following the light\nproduction behavior. A significant minority of meteors show large variations in\nRCS relative to the optical light curve over common height intervals,\nreflecting fragmentation or possibly differential ablation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Apr 2017 00:00:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-27"}
